This paper proposes a method for face hallucination using a generative adversarial network (GAN) and convolutional neural networks (CNN) to compensate for low and non-uniform illumination. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for image processing and enhancement. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (AI) methods for generating high-resolution images from low-resolution inputs. The paper also discusses multimedia (MM) applications for face hallucination and graphics (GR) techniques for image manipulation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.GR.
